1
00:00:10,600 --> 00:00:12,367
<i>After Regan was shot,
you saw him...</i>

2
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:14,033
<i>immediately being interviewed
by Mira.</i>

3
00:00:14,167 --> 00:00:16,033
<i>Currently,
the hostages are safe.</i>

4
00:00:16,167 --> 00:00:18,333
<i>The hostage taker,
Lieutenant Regan Robles,</i>

5
00:00:18,467 --> 00:00:20,067
<i> also surrendered.</i>

6
00:00:20,200 --> 00:00:22,200
<i> Noble, please save the Chief.</i>

7
00:00:22,333 --> 00:00:23,467
<i>Boss.
Mayor.</i>

8
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:25,567
<i>But unfortunately, he was shot.</i>

9
00:00:27,100 --> 00:00:28,067
<i> Bok, where did that come from?</i>

10
00:00:28,200 --> 00:00:29,567
<i> Conde! Robles!</i>

11
00:00:29,700 --> 00:00:31,167
<i>There was a shooter coming
from the outside,</i>

12
00:00:31,300 --> 00:00:33,100
<i> and he was killed immediately.</i>

13
00:00:33,233 --> 00:00:35,067
<i>Lieutenant Conde,
I'm going to the hospital now.</i>

14
00:00:35,233 --> 00:00:36,233
<i> Come with me.</i>

15
00:00:36,367 --> 00:00:38,400
<i> Captain, take your medicine.</i>

16
00:00:38,533 --> 00:00:39,633
<i> Hey, hey, hey, hey!</i>

17
00:00:39,767 --> 00:00:41,267
<i>You're a thief, aren't you?
You're a thief, right?</i>

18
00:00:41,400 --> 00:00:42,433
<i> This is Abdul!</i>

19
00:00:42,567 --> 00:00:45,100
<i>I'm the only goddess of beauty,
remember?</i>

20
00:00:45,233 --> 00:00:46,600
<i>- You're not leaving?
- Come on, drink your...</i>

21
00:00:46,733 --> 00:00:47,800
<i> You're not leaving?</i>

22
00:00:47,933 --> 00:00:48,767
<i> Bobby!</i>

23
00:00:48,900 --> 00:00:50,167
<i>- My grandchild!
- Ouch!</i>

24
00:00:50,300 --> 00:00:51,967
<i>- I can't see anything! Ouch!
- Bobby!</i>

25
00:00:52,100 --> 00:00:53,467
<i> When Regan was shot,</i>

26
00:00:53,600 --> 00:00:54,767
<i>well, there wasn't
even a hint...</i>

27
00:00:54,900 --> 00:00:56,333
<i>of shock or trauma on his face.</i>

28
00:00:56,467 --> 00:00:57,533
<i>Robles was just
right next to him.</i>

29
00:00:57,667 --> 00:00:59,567
<i>I'm a policeman,
and yet I was still shocked.</i>

30
00:00:59,700 --> 00:01:03,400
<i>I was just wondering because his
concern seemed fake.</i>

31
00:01:03,533 --> 00:01:05,000
<i> Tonyo!</i>

32
00:01:12,333 --> 00:01:14,100
Finally...

33
00:01:14,233 --> 00:01:17,633
World War 1 is over.

34
00:01:17,767 --> 00:01:18,700
Why don't I get a hug?

35
00:01:18,833 --> 00:01:20,933
I also responded.

36
00:01:21,067 --> 00:01:23,367
It's Robles?

37
00:01:23,500 --> 00:01:25,200
Yes, Bobby.

38
00:01:25,333 --> 00:01:28,867
He's the accomplice of the
syndicate at Station 12.

39
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:30,400
He must have sensed that he was
going to be caught,

40
00:01:30,533 --> 00:01:33,600
so he was immediately killed.

41
00:01:33,733 --> 00:01:36,600
Do you have any idea who the
head of this syndicate is?

42
00:01:36,733 --> 00:01:39,000
No, not yet.

43
00:01:39,133 --> 00:01:40,300
But...

44
00:01:40,467 --> 00:01:42,833
Tonyo is suspecting
someone already.

45
00:01:42,967 --> 00:01:44,767
It's Mayor Glen.

46
00:01:44,900 --> 00:01:48,133
He said earlier,
this, first of all...

47
00:01:48,267 --> 00:01:51,600
I didn't see any shock
or trauma in him.

48
00:01:51,733 --> 00:01:54,467
"As for me, a policeman, I was
still shocked."

49
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:56,133
Then he also said...

50
00:01:56,267 --> 00:02:00,333
"After shooting Robles, he
immediately gave an interview!"

51
00:02:00,467 --> 00:02:01,800
And this, wait a minute.

52
00:02:01,933 --> 00:02:04,100
And this. He also said...

53
00:02:04,233 --> 00:02:07,800
"I find his concern
for Robles fake.”

54
00:02:07,933 --> 00:02:09,733
That's it, right?
Right?

55
00:02:12,333 --> 00:02:13,967
Is that all, Tonyo?

56
00:02:16,700 --> 00:02:21,467
Sir Tonyo, at least our Mayor
now faces the people,

57
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:24,967
And he doesn't just pass on his
concern to whoever he wants.

58
00:02:25,100 --> 00:02:28,900
So, please, don't destroy
my brother's image, okay?

59
00:02:58,867 --> 00:03:00,267
Bobby...

60
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:02,567
I'm not destroying
the Mayor's character.

61
00:03:02,700 --> 00:03:06,700
I'm just telling him
my observations.

62
00:03:06,833 --> 00:03:10,400
Observations that are
all negative.

63
00:03:10,533 --> 00:03:13,633
Oh, okay, keep it up.

64
00:03:13,767 --> 00:03:16,033
I'm not saying
your brother is bad.

65
00:03:16,167 --> 00:03:19,200
Oh, but you're not saying
my brother is good either.

66
00:03:21,067 --> 00:03:24,267
You don't know Glen.

67
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:27,167
Why do you already know him?

68
00:03:27,300 --> 00:03:29,800
You just recently found out
that he's your brother.

69
00:03:29,933 --> 00:03:32,500
You defend him
as if you grew up together.

70
00:03:32,633 --> 00:03:34,567
Well then, it's you!

71
00:03:34,700 --> 00:03:36,267
You're the best!

72
00:03:36,400 --> 00:03:42,433
Oh yeah, you can't make mistakes
because you're the best.

73
00:03:42,567 --> 00:03:44,000
Let's go, Mar.

74
00:03:47,267 --> 00:03:49,333
Bobby!

75
00:03:49,467 --> 00:03:52,033
Why did he suddenly
get mad at you, Bok?

76
00:03:52,167 --> 00:03:53,200
Earlier, she was hugging you,

77
00:03:53,333 --> 00:03:55,733
and then suddenly,
she's mad at you.

78
00:03:57,800 --> 00:04:00,333
Bok. Bok.

79
00:04:03,700 --> 00:04:05,967
Your friend is really confusing.

80
00:04:06,100 --> 00:04:07,767
You're more confused!

81
00:04:07,900 --> 00:04:12,400
World War I just ended you
started World War II.

82
00:04:12,533 --> 00:04:14,567
You're stupid!

83
00:04:14,700 --> 00:04:16,933
You're such a blabbermouth.

84
00:04:17,067 --> 00:04:19,533
Oh, oh.

85
00:04:19,667 --> 00:04:22,267
Ouch!

86
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:24,367
Ouch! That hurts!

87
00:04:24,500 --> 00:04:25,467
Why...

88
00:04:25,600 --> 00:04:26,667
Ouch!

89
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:29,100
Ouch! Captain, that hurts!

90
00:04:29,267 --> 00:04:31,200
Oh my!

91
00:04:31,333 --> 00:04:33,467
What will happen to my beauty?

92
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:34,933
Captain!

93
00:04:35,067 --> 00:04:36,200
Captain!

94
00:04:36,333 --> 00:04:37,867
Hey, hey, hey, hey!

95
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,367
What do you think?

96
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:41,467
Did you think
that I'm not serious?

97
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:43,300
Did you think
it's just like that,

98
00:04:43,433 --> 00:04:44,700
you'd enter someone's house?

99
00:04:44,833 --> 00:04:46,467
It's Abdul! It's Abdul!
It's Abdul!

100
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:47,633
- What Abdul-Abdul?
- No, it's me!

101
00:04:47,767 --> 00:04:49,500
Get down there!
Get down there!

102
00:04:49,633 --> 00:04:51,700
Don't do anything bad!
Don't move!

103
00:04:51,833 --> 00:04:53,267
- Then don't!
- Don't move!

104
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:54,400
When my granddaughter comes,

105
00:04:54,533 --> 00:04:55,700
you're dead,
she's a police officer.

106
00:04:55,833 --> 00:04:57,367
- I'll have you locked up.
- I know Bobby...

107
00:04:57,500 --> 00:04:58,467
No, no, no.

108
00:04:58,600 --> 00:04:59,833
Get down.
You don't want?

109
00:04:59,967 --> 00:05:01,200
I'll hit you, I'll hit you.

110
00:05:01,367 --> 00:05:03,000
- Captain !
- No!

111
00:05:03,133 --> 00:05:04,300
There! There!

112
00:05:04,433 --> 00:05:06,300
Don't go anywhere!

113
00:05:06,433 --> 00:05:07,800
Captain !

114
00:05:07,933 --> 00:05:09,433
This is Abdul!

115
00:05:09,567 --> 00:05:10,800
Don't move.

116
00:05:10,933 --> 00:05:12,867
What? We're going to the market
together.

117
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:14,000
Going to the market?

118
00:05:14,133 --> 00:05:16,200
You're a thief, you animal!

119
00:05:16,333 --> 00:05:17,333
We are close!

120
00:05:17,467 --> 00:05:19,000
What close, close, close?

121
00:05:19,133 --> 00:05:21,167
You're a thief.

122
00:05:21,300 --> 00:05:24,233
I'll really beat you.

123
00:05:24,367 --> 00:05:26,767
- I'll beat you.
- Captain!

124
00:05:26,900 --> 00:05:29,100
Remember, I'm with Mar?

125
00:05:29,233 --> 00:05:30,633
You thought you could do
everything just

126
00:05:30,767 --> 00:05:31,967
because you're a man.

127
00:05:32,100 --> 00:05:34,133
Oh, Captain, even the feet?

128
00:05:34,300 --> 00:05:36,000
You can't escape me.

129
00:05:36,133 --> 00:05:37,633
Grandma, I won't run away!

130
00:05:37,767 --> 00:05:39,400
Stop! Stop!

131
00:05:39,533 --> 00:05:40,800
- Ouch!
- Stop it!

132
00:05:40,933 --> 00:05:41,967
You're a thief!

133
00:05:42,100 --> 00:05:43,733
- I'm not a thief.
- That's what you get.

134
00:05:43,867 --> 00:05:45,167
I live here!

135
00:05:45,300 --> 00:05:46,367
What do you mean you live here?

136
00:05:46,500 --> 00:05:48,500
Don't get up,

137
00:05:48,633 --> 00:05:50,400
- or else I'll beat you up.
- Yes, yes, yes.

138
00:05:50,533 --> 00:05:52,700
- Do you understand?
- Yes, yes, okay.

139
00:05:52,833 --> 00:05:55,700
Just stay there.

140
00:05:55,833 --> 00:05:57,833
Captain!

141
00:05:59,733 --> 00:06:02,100
Lord, I hope Bobby
and Mar will arrive soon.

142
00:06:04,133 --> 00:06:06,800
Her grandmother
is a hostage taker.

143
00:06:11,967 --> 00:06:14,633
Captain , this is Abdul!

144
00:06:17,867 --> 00:06:19,033
Sir Tonyo!

145
00:06:19,167 --> 00:06:21,833
What happened? I watched the
live feed of the hostage taking.

146
00:06:21,967 --> 00:06:25,133
Did anyone get hurt?

147
00:06:25,267 --> 00:06:28,667
It's Chief and Bautista,

148
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:30,133
they were both shot.

149
00:06:30,267 --> 00:06:32,767
What?

150
00:06:32,900 --> 00:06:34,767
Bok...

151
00:06:34,900 --> 00:06:36,233
Eric!

152
00:06:39,967 --> 00:06:41,167
Are you okay?

153
00:06:41,333 --> 00:06:43,567
I heard that some
policemen were hit.

154
00:06:43,700 --> 00:06:45,300
Are you okay? Are you not hurt?

155
00:06:45,433 --> 00:06:47,600
What? Not at all.

156
00:06:47,733 --> 00:06:49,233
- I'm okay.
- Okay.

157
00:06:49,367 --> 00:06:52,167
Bok, I'll leave you guys alone.

158
00:06:55,233 --> 00:06:57,000
Are you sure?
Nothing's wrong with you?

159
00:06:57,133 --> 00:06:58,033
I got nervous.

160
00:06:58,167 --> 00:06:59,767
I thought something
happened to you.

161
00:06:59,900 --> 00:07:01,967
The hostage taking was terrible.

162
00:07:04,567 --> 00:07:06,633
I'm okay.

163
00:07:10,667 --> 00:07:14,367
Bautista, you're not
seriously wounded.

164
00:07:14,533 --> 00:07:16,533
Just a few more days, you'll be
able to report for work.

165
00:07:16,667 --> 00:07:17,833
Yes, Ma'am.

166
00:07:20,967 --> 00:07:22,233
Ma'am Bobby.

167
00:07:22,367 --> 00:07:23,700
Thank you.

168
00:07:26,733 --> 00:07:28,233
Lieutenant Samson.

169
00:07:30,367 --> 00:07:32,067
Oh my...

170
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:35,633
that's why we're being
bashed in movies...

171
00:07:35,767 --> 00:07:37,200
because of people like you.

172
00:07:37,333 --> 00:07:38,800
The action is over,

173
00:07:38,933 --> 00:07:40,433
and that's when you'll show up.

174
00:07:40,567 --> 00:07:42,167
Lieutenant Samson,

175
00:07:42,300 --> 00:07:44,633
I'm not going
to answer you now, okay?

176
00:07:44,767 --> 00:07:46,133
I'm on leave,

177
00:07:46,267 --> 00:07:49,933
and besides,
I didn't come here for you.

178
00:07:50,100 --> 00:07:52,200
Bautista, how are you?

179
00:07:52,333 --> 00:07:54,067
Hey, you're not allowed
to die yet, huh?

180
00:07:54,200 --> 00:07:57,367
You're not yet
Lieutenant General...

181
00:07:57,500 --> 00:07:59,833
to have your life like that.

182
00:07:59,967 --> 00:08:02,133
Thank you, Ma'am Bobby.

183
00:08:02,267 --> 00:08:04,133
Until now, we still
can't figure out...

184
00:08:04,267 --> 00:08:06,967
why Lieutenant Robles did that.

185
00:08:07,100 --> 00:08:07,900
Yes, Ma'am.

186
00:08:08,033 --> 00:08:09,800
What's wrong with
Lieutenant Robles?

187
00:08:09,933 --> 00:08:12,700
Yes, and he suddenly shot Chief.

188
00:08:12,833 --> 00:08:14,433
Oh, okay,

189
00:08:14,567 --> 00:08:16,600
so you don't have to go through
any more trouble...

190
00:08:16,733 --> 00:08:22,433
I heard that Regan is connected
to Dante Eusebio,

191
00:08:22,600 --> 00:08:24,033
who is also connected
to the supplier...

192
00:08:24,167 --> 00:08:26,133
of pimple patch drugs...

193
00:08:26,267 --> 00:08:29,633
and is also connected
to Mandong Warak's escape.

194
00:08:29,767 --> 00:08:35,900
And Lieutenant Robles and Dante
Eusebio, they're just henchmen.

195
00:08:36,033 --> 00:08:39,133
There's definitely
a syndicate leader.

196
00:08:39,267 --> 00:08:41,333
And that syndicate leader,

197
00:08:41,467 --> 00:08:43,567
he's the one who had Lieutenant
Robles killed,

198
00:08:43,700 --> 00:08:46,733
And he's the one
we need to catch.

199
00:08:46,867 --> 00:08:48,867
In fairness to you,

200
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:50,600
you're up to date.

201
00:08:50,733 --> 00:08:52,167
But you know,
it would have been better...

202
00:08:52,300 --> 00:08:53,800
if you had come to the precinct.

203
00:08:53,933 --> 00:08:56,133
So you could have helped.

204
00:08:56,300 --> 00:08:59,333
Well, Bautista, I'll go ahead.

205
00:08:59,467 --> 00:09:01,200
Get well soon.

206
00:09:01,333 --> 00:09:03,200
I'll just go see Chief.

207
00:09:08,767 --> 00:09:10,900
She's such a smart-aleck,
isn't she?

208
00:09:11,033 --> 00:09:13,100
She's annoying!

209
00:09:13,233 --> 00:09:15,967
What? Where does it hurt?

210
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:19,067
It's okay.

211
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:21,767
Oh, there you go, you've got
your first remembrance.

212
00:09:21,900 --> 00:09:23,033
Congratulations.

213
00:09:23,167 --> 00:09:24,333
Congrats.

214
00:09:27,233 --> 00:09:30,367
Captain!

215
00:09:30,533 --> 00:09:33,033
Grandma doesn't want to hear me.

216
00:09:34,900 --> 00:09:35,567
Grandma!

217
00:09:35,700 --> 00:09:37,433
You're so noisy!

218
00:09:37,567 --> 00:09:38,667
You're so noisy!

219
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:39,767
Captain , I'm done
introducing myself.

220
00:09:39,900 --> 00:09:41,567
- I hope you recognize me.
- I know you.

221
00:09:41,700 --> 00:09:42,767
I'm Abdul!

222
00:09:42,900 --> 00:09:44,167
- Abdul the thief!
- No!

223
00:09:44,300 --> 00:09:46,500
Stop! Stop!
Don't be noisy!

224
00:09:46,633 --> 00:09:47,667
I'll give you some medicine!

225
00:09:47,800 --> 00:09:48,833
- You don't want to stop.
- Captain!

226
00:09:48,967 --> 00:09:50,200
Oh my!

227
00:09:50,333 --> 00:09:51,600
Captain!

228
00:09:51,733 --> 00:09:53,100
I'm here!

229
00:09:53,233 --> 00:09:55,000
- Thank you!
- I'm here!

230
00:09:55,133 --> 00:09:57,733
- Thank you, yes, yes.
- Thank you, Captain.

231
00:09:57,867 --> 00:10:01,100
Now stick that in your lungs!

232
00:10:01,267 --> 00:10:02,967
You're noisy.

233
00:10:03,100 --> 00:10:04,933
You're so noisy!

234
00:10:05,067 --> 00:10:06,300
Noisy!

235
00:10:06,433 --> 00:10:09,833
Well, that suits you.
That's better

236
00:10:09,967 --> 00:10:12,600
Oh, that, that, that.

237
00:10:12,733 --> 00:10:14,967
Oh, that's it.

238
00:10:15,100 --> 00:10:16,200
You're on your own.

239
00:10:16,333 --> 00:10:18,967
Cry all you want.

240
00:10:19,100 --> 00:10:20,567
Captain!

241
00:10:21,633 --> 00:10:23,067
Captain!

242
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:25,967
Let me go!

243
00:10:32,633 --> 00:10:33,800
What's taking him
too long to answer?

244
00:10:33,933 --> 00:10:35,367
As if he's busy...

245
00:10:35,533 --> 00:10:37,567
when he has nothing to do.

246
00:10:55,133 --> 00:10:56,733
Hello?

247
00:10:56,867 --> 00:10:59,833
Friend, why did it take so long
for you to answer?

248
00:10:59,967 --> 00:11:02,200
I have news for you!

249
00:11:02,333 --> 00:11:03,833
<i>- Hello?
- Friend!</i>

250
00:11:03,967 --> 00:11:06,033
Come home!

251
00:11:06,167 --> 00:11:09,267
Captian held me hostage!

252
00:11:09,433 --> 00:11:10,867
She even tied me up.

253
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:13,933
My god, I've been tied up
for some time now.

254
00:11:14,067 --> 00:11:15,867
Here's the thing,

255
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:18,667
Bobby, oh my god,

256
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:21,133
She and Tonyo are having
a lover's quarrel again.

257
00:11:21,267 --> 00:11:23,500
It seems like just a while ago
when we were there,

258
00:11:23,633 --> 00:11:26,233
She was worried about
the hostage taking.

259
00:11:26,367 --> 00:11:30,300
But when she arrived,
she immediately hugged him.

260
00:11:30,433 --> 00:11:32,233
I really wanted
to pull her hair!

261
00:11:32,367 --> 00:11:36,067
And when she let go,
she fought with him right away.

262
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:39,333
Bobby seems to be crazy, right?

263
00:11:39,467 --> 00:11:40,567
Hello?

264
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:42,333
Mar! Mar!

265
00:11:42,500 --> 00:11:44,000
I will really pull your hair.

266
00:11:44,133 --> 00:11:45,700
Listen to me first.

267
00:11:45,833 --> 00:11:48,167
I'm going to die here!

268
00:11:48,300 --> 00:11:50,967
Hello, Abdul?

269
00:11:51,100 --> 00:11:52,700
Hello?

270
00:11:56,200 --> 00:11:58,167
Oh, Girl, I'll go ahead.

271
00:11:58,300 --> 00:11:59,833
I'll talk to you later.

272
00:12:03,233 --> 00:12:04,367
Mar!

273
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:12,167
You're an animal!

274
00:12:12,300 --> 00:12:14,167
Mar!

275
00:12:22,233 --> 00:12:23,467
Mar!

276
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:24,867
Help!

277
00:12:34,500 --> 00:12:38,400
Oh, hello, I'm Mar.

278
00:12:38,533 --> 00:12:40,200
But you can call me Mary Anne.

279
00:12:40,333 --> 00:12:42,367
Perfect!

280
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:49,100
Mariano?

281
00:12:54,267 --> 00:12:56,600
Mariano Lumibao?

282
00:13:02,600 --> 00:13:05,133
Oh, wait, wait, wait!

283
00:13:05,267 --> 00:13:07,433
What's with you!

284
00:13:07,567 --> 00:13:08,600
Who are you?

285
00:13:08,733 --> 00:13:10,533
Don't you recognize me anymore?

286
00:13:10,667 --> 00:13:15,700
Donabel Mae Custudio,
4th Year, Atis!

287
00:13:15,833 --> 00:13:16,967
Donabel?

288
00:13:17,100 --> 00:13:21,067
It's me, your one and only ex
from high school!

289
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:22,700
Oh!

290
00:13:29,533 --> 00:13:31,467
Sir...

291
00:13:31,600 --> 00:13:32,933
- how are you?
- Sir.

292
00:13:33,067 --> 00:13:36,267
Oh, where's Garcia?

293
00:13:36,400 --> 00:13:38,500
Oh, Chief, he's with Selena.

294
00:13:38,633 --> 00:13:40,267
I just don't know
where they went.

295
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:44,700
Good thing,
and there's no noisy.

296
00:13:44,833 --> 00:13:46,533
I can rest.

297
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:51,300
Lieutenant Conde,
thank you very much.

298
00:13:51,433 --> 00:13:54,100
You didn't abandon my husband.

299
00:13:58,600 --> 00:14:00,233
It's not my time yet, Hon.

300
00:14:00,367 --> 00:14:01,367
What do you mean
it's not your time yet?

301
00:14:01,500 --> 00:14:03,133
You're just lucky.

302
00:14:03,267 --> 00:14:05,000
Maybe this happened to you,

303
00:14:05,133 --> 00:14:08,133
so you could slow down at work.

304
00:14:08,267 --> 00:14:09,233
In a way, you know,

305
00:14:09,367 --> 00:14:13,033
I'm glad you'll be with us
and the kids,

306
00:14:13,167 --> 00:14:16,133
and you'll be able to rest well.

307
00:14:16,267 --> 00:14:19,833
So you guys, spend time
with your family...

308
00:14:19,967 --> 00:14:22,300
because especially
in your profession,

309
00:14:22,433 --> 00:14:24,767
your one foot is in the grave.

310
00:14:24,900 --> 00:14:27,667
I know your job
is important to you,

311
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:33,567
but what's more important
than family?

312
00:14:33,733 --> 00:14:35,600
<i> How's grandma doing?</i>

313
00:14:35,733 --> 00:14:37,667
<i>It's possible
that she has dementia.</i>

314
00:14:37,800 --> 00:14:39,800
<i> Dementia?</i>

315
00:14:48,500 --> 00:14:50,600
Enriquez, what are you
doing there?

316
00:14:55,833 --> 00:14:56,967
Chief.

317
00:14:57,100 --> 00:14:59,500
Enriquez, how are you?

318
00:14:59,633 --> 00:15:02,167
Are you coming back?

319
00:15:02,333 --> 00:15:05,800
Oh, to be honest, Chief,

320
00:15:05,933 --> 00:15:09,733
I've been having second thoughts
the past few days.

321
00:15:09,867 --> 00:15:12,467
But when I heard your wife,

322
00:15:12,600 --> 00:15:14,567
I've made up my mind.

323
00:15:14,700 --> 00:15:16,200
Ma'am, you're right.

324
00:15:16,333 --> 00:15:19,267
There's nothing more important
than family.

325
00:15:24,067 --> 00:15:26,367
Chief, I've made up my mind.

326
00:15:28,500 --> 00:15:30,633
I'm going to resign, Chief.

327
00:15:40,933 --> 00:15:42,967
Enriquez...

328
00:15:43,100 --> 00:15:45,333
you never told me
anything like that.

329
00:15:45,467 --> 00:15:49,367
Why would I tell you?

330
00:15:49,500 --> 00:15:52,533
Well, because...

331
00:15:52,667 --> 00:15:54,367
we're friends.

332
00:15:57,667 --> 00:16:03,433
Chief, I'll just pass
my resignation letter to you.

333
00:16:03,567 --> 00:16:05,500
Get well soon.

334
00:16:05,633 --> 00:16:07,033
Okay, I'll go ahead.

335
00:16:07,167 --> 00:16:08,967
Okay.

336
00:16:16,567 --> 00:16:17,967
Oh...

337
00:16:18,100 --> 00:16:19,600
Major Flores is okay.

338
00:16:19,733 --> 00:16:22,167
There, oh, Boss Tonyo texted.

339
00:16:22,300 --> 00:16:25,800
It's a good thing none of our
Bosses at Station 12 got hurt.

340
00:16:25,933 --> 00:16:27,933
Isn't that right, Vince?

341
00:16:28,067 --> 00:16:29,100
Hey...

342
00:16:29,233 --> 00:16:31,667
- This guy is spaced out.
- Hey!

343
00:16:31,800 --> 00:16:33,600
Hey, you're playing
too hard to get.

344
00:16:33,733 --> 00:16:38,067
If you talk to Miss Faye, you
won't have any problems!

345
00:16:38,200 --> 00:16:39,100
You're annoying.

346
00:16:39,233 --> 00:16:41,300
I was told to stay away
from her, remember?

347
00:16:41,467 --> 00:16:44,100
Oh, you're afraid
of getting hurt again,

348
00:16:44,233 --> 00:16:47,133
so you're following
their orders.

349
00:16:47,267 --> 00:16:48,933
That's not it, Bro.

350
00:16:49,067 --> 00:16:52,567
Didn't I tell you,
we're used to being beaten?

351
00:16:52,700 --> 00:16:55,333
We're used to that.

352
00:16:55,467 --> 00:16:59,400
My only fear is that maybe later
on, they'll hurt Faye.

353
00:16:59,533 --> 00:17:02,033
That's not possible, Bro.

354
00:17:02,167 --> 00:17:03,800
Oh, okay, let's just say
you're right,

355
00:17:03,933 --> 00:17:05,833
that their family
did that to you.

356
00:17:05,967 --> 00:17:09,300
But do you think they can do
that to their own blood?

357
00:17:09,433 --> 00:17:12,000
Their own blood will get hurt
just because of you?

358
00:17:12,133 --> 00:17:15,400
Who are you? Are you handsome?

359
00:17:15,567 --> 00:17:20,800
Bro, we don't know
the guts of the rich.

360
00:17:20,933 --> 00:17:25,067
I know they'll find a way to
keep Faye away from me.

361
00:17:25,200 --> 00:17:28,800
They may take her
to a far away place.

362
00:17:28,933 --> 00:17:31,300
It's okay for me
that I see her from afar...

363
00:17:31,433 --> 00:17:34,633
rather than see her
leave completely.

364
00:17:34,767 --> 00:17:37,400
Why don't you approach
Faye's sister,

365
00:17:37,533 --> 00:17:38,833
- with Ma'am Bobby?
- Yes.

366
00:17:38,967 --> 00:17:41,567
After all, one day, she'll be
your sister-in-law.

367
00:17:41,700 --> 00:17:45,367
I know Boss Tonyo and Ma'am
Bobby are fighting.

368
00:17:45,500 --> 00:17:47,667
Maybe if I go near Ma'am Bobby,
maybe later,

369
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:51,333
She'll take out her anger on
Boss Tonyo on me.

370
00:17:59,100 --> 00:18:00,533
Bobby...

371
00:18:00,667 --> 00:18:02,333
Bobby, just a moment.

372
00:18:02,467 --> 00:18:04,333
Let's not fight.

373
00:18:04,467 --> 00:18:06,667
Let's talk.

374
00:18:06,800 --> 00:18:10,967
Tonyo, we don't have to patch
things up or even be friends.

375
00:18:11,100 --> 00:18:12,600
Okay,

376
00:18:12,733 --> 00:18:16,033
if you want us
just to be friends,

377
00:18:16,167 --> 00:18:18,867
but don't resign.

378
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:22,200
All your hard work
will be wasted.

379
00:18:22,367 --> 00:18:24,867
Besides, isn't this your dream?

380
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:27,800
Will you just turn
your back on it?

381
00:18:27,933 --> 00:18:29,833
I won't turn my back on it.

382
00:18:29,967 --> 00:18:32,667
I'll just fold it.

383
00:18:32,800 --> 00:18:36,267
Tonyo, my grandmother needs me.

384
00:18:36,400 --> 00:18:37,600
She has dementia.

385
00:18:37,733 --> 00:18:39,033
There's no cure for that,

386
00:18:39,167 --> 00:18:41,800
and it's getting worse.

387
00:18:41,933 --> 00:18:44,133
What's the use of me being a
successful police officer

388
00:18:44,267 --> 00:18:45,467
if she doesn't recognize me
anymore?

389
00:18:45,600 --> 00:18:47,800
That's no use anymore.

390
00:18:47,933 --> 00:18:49,633
I understand,

391
00:18:51,433 --> 00:18:54,867
but what about your finances?

392
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:56,600
It'll be harder for you to take
care of your grandmother...

393
00:18:56,767 --> 00:18:58,867
if you lose your job.

394
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:01,633
Father left me an inheritance.

395
00:19:01,767 --> 00:19:03,300
Oh, there you go.

396
00:19:03,433 --> 00:19:05,467
Why don't you just
get a caregiver...

397
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:08,167
so you can continue
your police work?

398
00:19:08,300 --> 00:19:11,300
Tonyo, why are you interfering
with my life?

399
00:19:11,433 --> 00:19:13,300
This is my strategy!

400
00:19:13,433 --> 00:19:15,533
Bobby, wait a minute.
It's not like that.

401
00:19:15,667 --> 00:19:17,533
Bobby,

402
00:19:19,933 --> 00:19:22,567
is Lieutenant Conde
bothering you?

403
00:19:26,667 --> 00:19:29,333
Not at all, Mayor.

404
00:19:29,500 --> 00:19:31,500
Okay, I'll go ahead.

405
00:19:41,767 --> 00:19:43,100
Tonyo...

406
00:19:43,700 --> 00:19:46,033
can I give you some advice?

407
00:19:47,100 --> 00:19:49,300
Just wait for Bobby
to cool down first.

408
00:19:49,433 --> 00:19:51,600
She can't ignore you.

409
00:19:52,367 --> 00:19:53,600
For now, you can...

410
00:19:53,733 --> 00:19:57,133
focus on finding out
who killed...

411
00:19:57,267 --> 00:19:58,667
Lieutenant Robles.

412
00:20:02,833 --> 00:20:04,833
Thank you, Mayor.

413
00:20:17,667 --> 00:20:20,200
Yes, I don't know about
those two.

414
00:20:20,333 --> 00:20:21,767
They patched things up,

415
00:20:21,900 --> 00:20:23,833
and then suddenly they started
fighting again.

416
00:20:23,967 --> 00:20:25,233
What were they fighting about?

417
00:20:25,367 --> 00:20:27,200
Why did they fight?

418
00:20:27,333 --> 00:20:29,067
Oh...

419
00:20:29,200 --> 00:20:30,533
Pride, pride.

420
00:20:30,667 --> 00:20:31,800
Probably pride.

421
00:20:31,933 --> 00:20:33,933
They're always like that.

422
00:20:34,067 --> 00:20:35,200
Oh, wait, just a moment, huh?

423
00:20:35,367 --> 00:20:36,467
Let me just answer this.

424
00:20:36,600 --> 00:20:38,867
Peach, she's been asking me
about this pageant.

425
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:41,033
- Wait a minute.
- Pageant?

426
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:43,633
Hello, babe?

427
00:20:43,767 --> 00:20:46,733
Well, I'm not sure yet.

428
00:20:46,867 --> 00:20:48,500
I'll get back to you
within the day, okay?

429
00:20:48,633 --> 00:20:50,100
I'll tell you.

430
00:20:50,233 --> 00:20:51,500
Oh, okay, okay.

431
00:20:51,633 --> 00:20:53,467
Okay, bye.

432
00:20:56,967 --> 00:20:58,600
Oh...

433
00:20:58,733 --> 00:21:00,400
Pageant, isn't...

434
00:21:00,533 --> 00:21:03,033
there are swimsuit competitions,

435
00:21:03,167 --> 00:21:05,600
the ones with the girls
in two piece swimsuits?

436
00:21:05,733 --> 00:21:07,333
Yes, something like that.

437
00:21:07,467 --> 00:21:09,567
Oh, is that so?

438
00:21:10,067 --> 00:21:12,167
Oh, wait, why are you reacting
like that?

439
00:21:12,300 --> 00:21:12,967
You don't like pageants?

440
00:21:13,100 --> 00:21:14,533
Do you have a problem with that?

441
00:21:14,667 --> 00:21:16,133
Oh, no, no, no.

442
00:21:16,267 --> 00:21:19,000
Those pageants are okay with me,

443
00:21:19,133 --> 00:21:22,167
- but...
- You've got a lot of excuses.

444
00:21:22,300 --> 00:21:23,300
Oh, okay, I'll change
the question.

445
00:21:23,433 --> 00:21:24,267
Suppose you have a girlfriend,

446
00:21:24,400 --> 00:21:26,100
and she wants to join
the pageant.

447
00:21:26,233 --> 00:21:27,733
What, would you let her join,
or not?

448
00:21:27,867 --> 00:21:29,767
You'd forbid her, wouldn't you?

449
00:21:29,900 --> 00:21:32,800
If she wants,
I'll support her, go.

450
00:21:32,933 --> 00:21:34,567
Really? Even though it's obvious

451
00:21:34,700 --> 00:21:36,167
that you really don't want it?

452
00:21:38,100 --> 00:21:40,033
She's my girlfriend.

453
00:21:40,167 --> 00:21:44,067
Of course, I'll support her in
whatever she wants, even if...

454
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:46,300
I don't want it.

455
00:21:46,433 --> 00:21:48,467
If that's what makes her happy.

456
00:21:50,567 --> 00:21:51,933
Okay.

457
00:21:55,033 --> 00:21:56,733
Hello, Peach?

458
00:21:57,167 --> 00:21:59,633
Okay, I won't join.

459
00:21:59,767 --> 00:22:01,467
Take care, do your best!

460
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:03,667
All right, bye.

461
00:22:09,667 --> 00:22:11,767
Would you like to have coffee?

462
00:22:11,900 --> 00:22:13,200
Let's go.

463
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:30,167
Boss?

464
00:22:30,300 --> 00:22:31,333
Hello?

465
00:22:31,467 --> 00:22:32,667
You saw it.

466
00:22:32,800 --> 00:22:35,167
Did you know I thought
I was going to fail?

467
00:22:35,300 --> 00:22:36,800
You know, I haven't done it
in a while.

468
00:22:36,933 --> 00:22:38,233
A bit rusty, you know.

469
00:22:38,367 --> 00:22:40,400
But you saw it, Boss.

470
00:22:40,533 --> 00:22:42,567
One shot, one kill.

471
00:22:42,700 --> 00:22:44,167
Problem solved.

472
00:22:44,300 --> 00:22:46,200
Good job...

473
00:22:46,333 --> 00:22:48,133
but don't be so arrogant.

474
00:22:48,300 --> 00:22:50,100
You just got lucky.

475
00:22:50,233 --> 00:22:53,233
Oh, Boss, by the way,

476
00:22:53,367 --> 00:22:56,900
maybe I can ask for a little
bonus for that?

477
00:22:57,033 --> 00:23:00,533
Next time, when everything
is ironed out.

478
00:23:00,667 --> 00:23:01,833
Right now,
someone is still looking

479
00:23:01,967 --> 00:23:04,967
for who ordered Lieutenant
Robles's death.

480
00:23:05,100 --> 00:23:07,833
They won't find out.

481
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:10,800
<i> Who among them?</i>

482
00:23:10,933 --> 00:23:12,900
It's Conde.

483
00:23:13,033 --> 00:23:15,233
I should have killed him
with Regan.

484
00:23:15,367 --> 00:23:16,900
<i> Not yet.</i>

485
00:23:17,033 --> 00:23:19,167
There's a right time for that.

486
00:23:19,300 --> 00:23:21,900
Let's not waste our time on him.

487
00:23:23,433 --> 00:23:27,633
What's the news about
our investors?

488
00:23:27,767 --> 00:23:28,800
Oh...

489
00:23:28,933 --> 00:23:31,800
Oh, according to Okoy, he said
everything is fine.

490
00:23:31,933 --> 00:23:34,167
<i>Most of the people who come
are big customers.</i>

491
00:23:34,300 --> 00:23:36,900
But we need to make
the pageant bigger.

492
00:23:37,033 --> 00:23:38,800
No problem.

493
00:23:38,933 --> 00:23:43,967
As long as the return on
investment is big, that's okay.

494
00:23:44,100 --> 00:23:45,767
Okay, boss.

495
00:24:02,700 --> 00:24:04,500
I'm just training these guys.

496
00:24:04,633 --> 00:24:05,767
I need to impress.

497
00:24:05,900 --> 00:24:08,833
You don't need to lie
just to impress.

498
00:24:08,967 --> 00:24:10,567
There are so many things
to like about you.

499
00:24:10,700 --> 00:24:11,867
Sir Tonyo, help us!

500
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:13,800
It's an emergency,
we need you.

501
00:24:13,933 --> 00:24:15,533
Is this the emergency
you're talking about?

502
00:24:15,667 --> 00:24:18,367
Fashion emergency is still
an emergency.

503
00:24:18,500 --> 00:24:20,733
We need your expert opinion.

504
00:24:20,867 --> 00:24:23,467
Look at this post that Tonyo
is tagged in.

505
00:24:23,600 --> 00:24:24,533
Oh, winner!

506
00:24:24,667 --> 00:24:26,567
Hey friend,
we can't blame Tonyo.

507
00:24:26,700 --> 00:24:27,533
Does it hurt?

508
00:24:27,667 --> 00:24:29,167
It hurts more when I hit you.

509
00:24:29,333 --> 00:24:30,633
- Step aside!
- Let's party!

510
00:24:30,767 --> 00:24:31,833
Donabelle!

511
00:24:33,233 --> 00:24:34,400
What did you do to her?

512
00:24:34,533 --> 00:24:35,400
Stay away from her!

513
00:24:35,533 --> 00:24:36,833
Apple, call the police, quick!

514
00:24:36,967 --> 00:24:38,733
Tell them they killed
Miss Donabelle!

515
00:24:38,867 --> 00:24:40,767
Don't worry,
I'll help you.

516
00:24:40,900 --> 00:24:42,600
Aren't you officially on leave,

517
00:24:42,733 --> 00:24:44,633
and then you'll resign?

518
00:24:44,767 --> 00:24:46,300
How can you help?
